Creating Dimension 9

Click on Master item then click on Dimension and select Create new. A dialog box will open. Select Drill-down for the dimension type and type Category under field. 

DeptPosition

Click on Master item then click on Dimension and select Create new.

A dialog box will open. Select Drill-down for the dimension type 

Type Department under search then click to add it

Type Position and select it under field to add it to your drill-down

Lastly click on Create to create the drill-down dimension



DeptPositionEmp

Click on Master item then click on Dimension and select Create new.

A dialog box will open. Select Drill-down for the dimension type 

Type Department under search then click to add it

Type Position and select it under field to add it to your drill-down

Add Employee_Name as the last field

Lastly click on Create to create the drill-down dimension


GenAgeRange

Click on Master item then click on Dimension and select Create new.

A dialog box will open. Select Drill-down for the dimension type 

Type Generation under search then click to add it

Type AgeRange and select it under field to add it to your drill-down

Lastly click on Create to create the drill-down dimension


YearMonthDD

Go to the data manager and click on the icon that looks like a pen to edit the table.

Go to DateofTermination and change the data type to Date. Use the gif below as a guide.

Load the data when you complete that step.


Click on Master item then click on Dimension and select Create new.

A dialog box will open. Select Drill-down for the dimension type 

Type and select DateofTermination.autoCalender.Year under search then click to add it

Type DateofTermination.autoCalender.Month and select it under field to add it to your drill-down

Type and select DateofTermination and add it to the DD

Next change the name to YearMonthDD

Lastly click on Create to create the drill-down dimension
